data.name: Sample - ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP - 1.0.0
data.description: Sample playbooks for "ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP" connector. If you are planning to use any of the sample playbooks in your environment, ensure that you clone those playbooks and move them to a different collection, since the sample playbook collection gets deleted during connector upgrade and delete.

workflows.name: Update FortiSOARs Incident
workflows.description: Update FortiSOAR's record with ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP Request details

workflows.name: Get All Tickets
workflows.description: Retrieves details of all tickets or specific tickets from ServiceDesk Plus based on the input parameters you have specified.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Get All Tickets

workflows.name: Create Ticket
workflows.description: Creates a ticket in ServiceDesk Plus based on the requester, subject, and other input parameters you have specified and an incident record is also created in the FortiSOAR

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Create Ticket

workflows.name: Get Ticket Details
workflows.description: Retrieves details of a specific ticket from ServiceDesk Plus based on the ticket request ID you have specified.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Get Ticket Details

workflows.name: Update Ticket
workflows.description: Updates an existing ticket in ServiceDesk Plus based on the ticket request ID and other input parameters you have specified.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Update Ticket

workflows.name: Close Ticket
workflows.description: Closes a ticket in ServiceDesk Plus based on the ticket request ID and other input parameters you have specified.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Close Ticket

workflows.name: Delete Ticket
workflows.description: Deletes a ticket (moves it to 'trash') from ServiceDesk Plus based on the ticket request ID you have specified.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Delete Ticket

workflows.name: Delete Ticket From Trash
workflows.description: Permanently deletes a ticket from the 'Trash' in ServiceDesk Plus based on the Ticket Request ID you have specified.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Delete Ticket From Trash

workflows.name: Add Note
workflows.description: Adds a note to an existing ticket in ServiceDesk Plus based on the ticket request ID, description, and other input parameters you have specified.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Add Note

workflows.name: Add Resolution
workflows.description: Adds a resolution to an existing ticket in ServiceDesk Plus based on the ticket request ID and resolution you have specified.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Add Resolution

workflows.name: Get All Users
workflows.description: Retrieves details of all users or specific user from ServiceDesk Plus based on the input parameters you have specified.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Get All Users

workflows.name: Get All Accounts
workflows.description: Retrieves information of all accounts details Service Desk Plus MSP.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Get All Accounts

workflows.name: Get All Sites
workflows.description: Retrieves information of all site details Service Desk Plus MSP.

arguments.title: ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus MSP: Get All Sites
